# Coding Principles

## Core Principles

- **Micro-Files**: Limit files to ~300 lines. Refactor into smaller modules if exceeded.
- **Guard Clauses**: Return early instead of nesting if/else structures.
- **DRY**: Extract reusable logic into `lib/` or shared utilities. Never duplicate logic across files.
- **No Magic Strings**: Use constants in `constants/` for repeated values (venue types, scoring weights, status labels, etc.).
- **Strict Typing**: Never use `any`. Define interfaces/types in `types/` for all data structures, API responses, and component props.

## State & Rendering (React/Next.js)

- **Server Components First**: Default to Server Components. Only add `"use client"` when the component needs hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs.
- **Data Fetching**: Fetch data server-side in page/layout components; pass results as props to client components.

## Design & Performance

- **Interaction Feedback**: Every user action (click, submit, toggle) must provide visual feedback within 400ms — use loading spinners, optimistic updates, or disabled states.
- **Semantic HTML**: Use `<main>`, `<section>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, `<button>` over generic `<div>` elements.
- **Accessibility**: Include proper ARIA labels, roles, and keyboard navigation on all interactive elements.

## Feature-Based Folder Structure

```
app/
├── page.tsx                            # Dashboard
├── leads/
│   ├── page.tsx                        # Discovery & lead list
│   └── [placeId]/page.tsx              # Lead detail + enrichment
├── outreach/page.tsx                   # Email drafts queue
├── pipeline/page.tsx                   # Pipeline tracker
├── settings/page.tsx                   # Brand voice config
└── api/
    ├── leads/
    ├── outreach/
    ├── pipeline/
    └── notifications/
components/
├── ui/                                 # shadcn/ui primitives
├── layout/                             # sidebar, header
└── features/
    ├── leads/                          # lead-card, lead-list, discovery-form, score-badge
    ├── outreach/                       # email-preview
    ├── pipeline/
    ├── settings/
    └── notifications/                  # notification-badge, notification-panel
lib/                                    # API clients, services, utilities
constants/                              # Typed constants (no magic strings)
types/                                  # Shared TypeScript interfaces
data/                                   # Seed data (JSON)
```

- Group components, hooks, and logic **by feature**, not by type.
- **No barrel files** (`index.ts` re-exports). Always use direct imports.
- Keep feature folders self-contained: a feature's components, hooks, and helpers live together.
